Question: What is an IDE?
Answer:
• An IDE (Integrated Development Environment) is a software that helps to edit and compile code easily.
• It puts everything a programmer needs in one place — like a code editor, compiler, and debugger.
• It gives auto-complete suggestions.
• It helps find errors quickly using a debugger.
• It manage files and projects in an organized way.

What an IDE includes:
• Code editor (for writing code)
• Compiler or interpreter (to run the code)
• Debugger (to fix mistakes)
• Project explorer (to manage files)

Examples of IDEs:
• Visual Studio (C#, .NET)
• VS Code (multi-language support)
• Eclipse (Java)
• PyCharm (Python)
• IntelliJ IDEA (Java/Kotlin)
